"{\"content\":{\"body\":\"*Original post from [makzan.substack.com](https://makzan.substack.com/p/2022-week-1-accessibility-design)*, repost here.\\n\\nHi there,\\n\\nIt‚Äôs the first week of 2022. Yes, according to [ISO8601](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601), this is the first week of 2022.\\n\\nHere are the links worth sharing this week:\\n\\n**‚Üí UI Design / [The good, the bad and the toggle](https://www.alexbuenodesign.com/blog/the_good_the_bad_and_the_toogle)**\\n\\n> *If the toggle is an action (Play/Pause) the label/title should show what will happen. If the toggle is an option (On/Off) then it should show the current state.*\\n\\n![](https://miro.medium.com/max/1400/0\\\\*oREZaxOidTVHvpHi.png)\\n\\n**‚Üí Accessibility / [Why We Need More Accessibility Designers by Anna E. Cook](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dQVrfS74xyM)**\\n\\nYou don‚Äôt have to have the title of ‚Äúaccessibility designer‚Äù to make your designs more accessible.\\n\\n![](https://miro.medium.com/max/1400/0\\\\*o9sSdpMEqdJKGT3M.jpeg)\\n\\n**‚Üí Accessibility / [Twitter needs manual language selection](https://hiddedevries.nl/en/blog/2021-12-30-twitter-needs-manual-language-selection)**\\n\\nSetting the language is important for end users, like:\\n\\n* people who use a screenreader to read out content on a page\\n* people who use a braille display\\n* people who end up seeing a default font (browsers can select these based on language)\\n* people who use software to translate content\\n* people who want to right click a word in our content to look it up in a dictionary\\n* people who use user stylesheets\\n\\nFor non-English tweets to meet WCAG, they need to have their language declared with a lang attribute. Twitter currently guesses languages, which is a great step in the right direction, but is likely of little help to speakers of minority languages. A manual selector would be a great way to complement the automation.\\n\\n![](https://miro.medium.com/max/1400/0\\\\*GyPrfM6cfKvbBnzx.jpeg)\\n\\n**‚Üí CSS and Accessibility / [CSS Underlines Are Too Thin and Too Low in Chrome](https://css-tricks.com/css-underlines-are-too-thin-and-too-low-in-chrome/)**\\n\\nDefault underlines are inconsistent\\n\\n![](https://miro.medium.com/max/1400/0\\\\*X1igRGwqKqmoVxSU.jpeg)\\n\\n**‚Üí CSS, Accessibility / [Should CSS Override Default Browser Styles?](https://css-tricks.com/should-css-override-default-styles/)**\\n\\nThe lines are relatively fuzzy, but I‚Äôd say there is nothing in CSS that should be outright banned from use ‚Äî it‚Äôs more about the styling choices you make. So when you do choose to style something, it remains usable and accessible. Heck, background-color can be terribly abused making for inaccessible and unusable areas of a site, but nobody raises pitchforks over that.\\n\\n**‚Üí JS Lib / [VantaJS](https://www.vantajs.com/)**\\n\\nAnimated and Interactive background via WebGL. Each effect can be further customized to fit the website‚Äôs style.\\n\\n![](https://miro.medium.com/max/1400/0\\\\*m13WzV2OLhtjluTi.jpeg)\\n\\n**‚Üí Product Development / [Hard Edges, Soft Middle](https://www.colemanm.org/post/hard-edges-soft-middle/)**\\n\\n![](https://miro.medium.com/max/1400/0\\\\*oCJNyqRgO5ezMTUM.jpeg)\\n\\nBy defining a hard boundary within 6 weeks, we trust the developers to come up with solutions.\\n\\n> *This requires trust in the product team to choose approach trade-offs wisely. If you encounter a library in use for the feature that‚Äôs heavily out of date, but the version update requires sweeping changes throughout the app, you‚Äôll need to pick your battles. A team with fixations on particular steps (the ‚Äúhard middle‚Äù) might decide too early that an adjacent feature needs rework. Before pulling up to a higher altitude to look at the entire forest, the team‚Äôs already hitched to a particular step.*\\n\\n![](https://miro.medium.com/max/1400/0\\\\*bE8m1ar0Yqxdwhbx.jpeg)\\n\\n**‚Üí JS / [console.assert](https://twitter.com/wesbos/status/1478439959543656454)**\\n\\n[https://twitter.com/wesbos/status/1478439959543656454](https://twitter.com/wesbos/status/1478439959543656454)\\n\\n> üî• You can use console.assert() as a cheap-n-easy test function\\n\\n![](https://miro.medium.com/max/1400/0\\\\*Vcrzu53md_dBkIe4.png)\\n\\n## Quote of the week\\n\\n> *‚Äúif an explanation can help that person start to care, the rest is much easier.‚Äù*¬†\\n\\n![](https://images.mirror-media.xyz/publication-images/mSuhu6rdRS5o1mYiaFd2O.png?height=393&width=700)\\n\\nUntil next week,  \\n Makzan\\n\\n\\n---\\n\\n**About Makzan‚Äôs Weekly Newsletter**\\n\\nI collect web development and accessibility posts every week.\",\"timestamp\":1641742918,\"title\":\"2022 Week 1 ‚Äî Accessibility Design, CSS Styles and Accessibility, Interactive Animated Background Library, console.assert()\"},\"digest\":\"r3fXURapFa8qjytUciFwp77mo8cyFu7cQh75fEWqbV0\",\"authorship\":{\"contributor\":\"0xC6a9a8a30c5f9Aa83519Fd4D36fb52BF3F88B6d3\",\"signingKey\":\"{\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_ops\\\":[\\\"verify\\\"],\\\"kty\\\":\\\"EC\\\",\\\"x\\\":\\\"ELUwijw4wZNuctWWqVhCjOj4UxZkIpN9eRRbxWJd9LA\\\",\\\"y\\\":\\\"GTijIICEzc_pvY6KHtcyg-DvHoWhvLEoa6JCNaf7JIs\\\"}\",\"signature\":\"UzhXas_fR1F7O21Ut-Y2NclK1P_Nko8Ij30kiXqsITQql1LuqsXItZ-WsZj40pM2LoqKaxU4O5-aGQ9qHKnMaQ\",\"signingKeySignature\":\"0xa5ef01e37dc676158b3bcd96be0c26554464bdb7ff3e9fd320abe9534ceac7e16dab2d913e123357699fc009a6471160d441d032984419405fe8e7bb33c7a0dc1c\",\"signingKeyMessage\":\"I authorize publishing on mirror.xyz from this device using:\\n{\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_ops\\\":[\\\"verify\\\"],\\\"kty\\\":\\\"EC\\\",\\\"x\\\":\\\"ELUwijw4wZNuctWWqVhCjOj4UxZkIpN9eRRbxWJd9LA\\\",\\\"y\\\":\\\"GTijIICEzc_pvY6KHtcyg-DvHoWhvLEoa6JCNaf7JIs\\\"}\",\"algorithm\":{\"name\":\"ECDSA\",\"hash\":\"SHA-256\"}},\"nft\":{},\"version\":\"12-21-2020\",\"originalDigest\":\"AA4k5RjgRMjhunxsmd8E0RbrJAJG4h5LaRzUfAypMS0\"}"